('update_check', 'a:4:{s:10:\"last_check\";i:1516064291;s:14:\"latest_version\";s:64:\"<span style=\"color: #C00;\"><strong>1.8.14</strong> (1814)</span>\";s:19:\"latest_version_code\";i:1814;s:4:\"news\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:\"title\";s:27:\"MyBB Support Policy Changes\";s:11:\"description\";s:358:\"Following a recent discussion on the MyBB Community Forums regarding the Support Eligibility Policy, we have decided to make some changes to how we determine if we provide support to users. The previous Support Eligibility Policy was unclear in many circumstances. There were many edge cases and grey areas where it was unclear why a user may be [&#8230;]\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/MyBBDevelopmentBlog/~3/EXX7g3Vy8kg/\";s:6:\"author\";s:3:\"Ben\";s:8:\"dateline\";i:1515343866;}i:1;a:5:{s:5:\"title\";s:59:\"MyBB 1.8.14 Released — Security &amp; Maintenance Release\";s:11:\"description\";s:379:\"MyBB 1.8.14 is now available, and is a security &#38; maintenance release. This update applies security patches and fixes minor issues related to the upgrade script included in the previous version. 2 security vulnerabilities addressed: High risk: Language file headers RCE &#8212; reported by Julian Rittweger Low risk: Language Pack Properties XSS &#8212; reported by [&#8230;]\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/MyBBDevelopmentBlog/~3/FJVpWzB0Q5o/\";s:6:\"author\";s:12:\"Devilshakerz\";s:8:\"dateline\";i:1511882195;}i:2;a:5:{s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"MyBB 1.8 Dockerfile &amp; Docker Compose Recipe\";s:11:\"description\";s:227:\"With the recent announcements of the 1.10 branch we\'ve also got some great news for both plugin developers and theme designers. In recent weeks, work has been underway to create an official Docker image for the MyBB 1.8 series.\";s:4:\"link\";s:66:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/MyBBDevelopmentBlog/~3/YbQsXwOgudY/\";s:6:\"author\";s:6:\"Euan T\";s:8:\"dateline\";i:1511605160;}}}'),
