(58, 'Mladost wins in Water polo Classic', '', '2017-10-22', '<p><img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Partizan-Mladostfoto-v-markovic-2944.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>Only two clubs remain unbeaten after two rounds in Group&nbsp; A1 of the 2017/18 Regional League. Title-holder Jug Dubrovnik and its archrival in Croatia Mladost Zagreb have six points each</p>\n\n<p>Round 2 was opened by one of the &ldquo;water polo classics&rdquo;. Mladost Zagreb and Partizan, which were the two best water polo clubs of the world in the 20th century, met in Belgrade. The first quarter determined the rest of the encounter. Mladost started like a storm. The Croats, led by Luka Bukic, jumped to 4:0 in the seventh minute (Bukic scored three of four). The young team from Belgrade started climbing back and trailed 3:5 early in the third period, but Mladost controlled the match till the end and won 9:5.</p>\n\n<p>Jug was too strong for Jadran Split, the quarter-finalist of the Euro Cup. Jug built a five-goal lead until the 17th minute (6:1). Jadran managed to come close to the hosts in the finish of the third period (8:5). After that, Jug netted five straight goals for a convincing win (13:5).</p>\n\n<p>Primorje beat Budva water polo players, as a guest, in a last-second drama. The team from Rijeka dominated in the first half. Budva its only goal in the first half scored in the 13th minute (when Porobic netted for 1:3). Primorje went 5:1 up in the second minute of the third period. But soon everything turned around. Budva responded with four goals in a row and managed to equalise &ndash; 5:5 (5:18 before the end). There were a lot of chances on both sides in the remaining five minutes. The decision came in the last second when Tkac converted an extra-man attack. The guests won 6:5, despite Budva held Primorje scoreless for 14:48 minutes of the second half.</p>\n\n<p>As expected, Jadran Herceg Novi beat POSK. The team from Herceg Novi led 4:2 at half-time. After the 5-minute break, Jadran ruled the field and achieved a solid 10:4 win.</p>\n\n<p>Mornar Split achieved its first victory of the season beating Primorac. Mornar had a three-goal lead in the third period (6:3, 8:5, 9:6). Primorac reduced the gap in the fourth (9:8), but the hosts kept the advantage for a 10:8 win.</p>\n\n<p>The 2nd round in Group A2 was highlighted by a Serbian derby. In a thrilling encounter Red Star (Crvena Zvezda) defeated Vojvodina 10:9 (2:1, 3:3, 2:2, 3:3).</p>\n\n<h2>REGIONAL LEAGUE, 2ND ROUND</h2>\n\n<h4>GROUP A1</h4>\n\n <h6 >PARTIZAN 5:9 MLADOST<br />\n(1:4, 0:1, 3:2, 1:2)</h6>\n\n<p>Partizan: Dj. Lazic 2, Lukic, M. Jankovic, Vucinic.<br />\nMladost: Bukic 3, Basic 2, Radu, Zovic, F. Lazic, Markovic.</p>\n\n <h6 >JUG 13:5 JADRAN S<br />\n(3:1, 2:0, 4:4, 4:0)</h6>\n\n<p>Jug: Ivankovic 3, Macan 2, Fatovic 2, Renzuto 2, Jokovic, Rasovic, Benic, Lozina.<br />\nJadran Split: Power 2, Butic, Krapic, Antonijevic.</p>\n\n <h6 >JADRAN HN 10:4 POSK<br />\n(3:1, 1:1, 2:1, 4:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Jadran Herceg Novi: Merkulov 2, Petkovic 2, Popadic, Gardasevic, Radovic, Spajic, Draskovic, Mijuskovic.<br />\nPOSK: Situm, Elez, Delic, Butic.</p>\n\n <h6 >BUDVA 5:6 PRIMORJE<br />\n(0:2, 1:2, 3:1, 1:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Budva: Mitrovic 2, Porobic, Adzic, N. Popovic.<br />\nPrimorje: Tkac 2, Cunko, Peros, Blazic, Mudrazija.</p>\n\n <h6 >MORNAR 10:8 PRIMORAC<br />\n(1:2, 4:1, 4:3, 1:2)</h6>\n\n<p>Mornar: Duzevic 3, Buha 2, Cagalj, Goreta, Calic, Zivkovic, Buric.<br />\nPrimorac: Gluhaic 2, Vukmirovic 2, Paunovic 2, Gopcevic, Grgurevic.</p>\n\n<p>1 Jug (Croatia) 2 games -6 points<br />\n2 Mladost (Croatia) 2 &ndash; 6<br />\n3 Jadran HN (Montenegro) 2 &ndash; 3<br />\n4 Partizan (Serbia) 2 &ndash; 3<br />\n5 Primorje (Croatia) 2 &ndash; 3<br />\n6 Jadran S (Croatia) 2 &ndash; 3<br />\n7 Mornar (Croatia) 2 &ndash; 3<br />\n8. POSK (Croatia) 2 &ndash; 3<br />\n9 Primorac (Montenegro) 2 &ndash; 0<br />\n10 Budva (Montenegro) 2 &ndash; 0</p>\n\n<h2>GROUP A2</h2>\n\n<p>Crvena Zvezda &ndash; Vojvodina 10:9<br />\nZadar &ndash; Valjevo 8:11<br />\nSolaris &ndash; Nais 6:9<br />\nCattaro &ndash; Medvescak 10:10</p>\n\n<p>1 Valjevo (Serbia) 2 &ndash; 6<br />\n2 Crvena zvezda (Serbia) 2 &ndash; 6<br />\n3 Vojvodina (Serbia) 2 &ndash; 3<br />\n4 Sabac (Serbia) 1 &ndash; 3<br />\n5 Nais (Serbia) 2 &ndash; 3<br />\n6 Cattaro (Montenegro) 2 &ndash; 1<br />\n7 Medvescak (Croatia) 2 &ndash; 1<br />\n8 Zadar 1952 (Croatia) 1 &ndash; 0<br />\n9. Solaris (Croatia) 2 &ndash; 0</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(59, 'Sabadell debuts on the main stage', '', '2017-10-23', '<p><img alt=\"Brescia water polo player Presciutti Nicholas in the pool\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Brescia-Presciutti-Nicholas.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>OSC (Hungary), Brescia (Italy), Jadran (Montenegro) and Sabadell (Spain) joined wild-card holders in the Preliminary Round of the 2017/18 Champions League. The four clubs passed hard exams in the third qualification round and secured their places on the main stage. The second leg of the Qualification round 3, played today, saw three close victories and one convincing win.</p>\n\n<p>Brescia, OSC and Jadran have already played in the Champions League by a new format (introduced 2013), while Sabadell will make its debut. After a tie against Red Star (Crvena Zvezda) in Belgrade (6:6), the Spaniards beat the Serbs 11:8 in the second match today. It wasn&rsquo;t so easy. Red Star, that surprised by reaching the Qualification Round 3, led 3:2 in the opening minute of the second period. By the middle of the third quarter, the hosts built a three-goal advantage for the first time (7:4). Sabadell was 10:6 up 4:45 before the last buzzer, but the guests didn&rsquo;t give up. The young players from Belgrade scored twice in a span of 60 seconds and came close once more &ndash; 10:8 (03:16 remaining on the clock), but they weren&rsquo;t able to reduce the gap any further. Cabanas&rsquo; goal decided everything 1:25 before the end.</p>\n\n<p>Brescia water polo players came in Kazan with a two-goal advantage earned in the first match against Sintez, in their&nbsp;pool (9:7). The Italians took a flying start today, they had a 5:0 lead in the 17th minute of the encounter. It seemed that they would beat the hosts convincingly, but the Russians didn&rsquo;t let them celebrate too early. In the second half, Sintez was reducing its deficit step-by-step. The hosts managed to equalise twice (6:6 and 7:7), but they didn&rsquo;t gain a lead until the last minute when Zakirov scored for the final score 8:7. But it was too late, 13 seconds before the end. Sintez won the game, but Brescia went through.</p>\n\n<p>Jadran Herceg Novi defeated Marseille once more. On Saturday, they celebrated a close 7:6 win in France. Today, they beat the French 9:7 in Herceg Novi. It was another balanced match. The Montenegrins had a 2:0 opening lead, but Marseille stroke back and turned around an early deficit to a slim 4:3 lead in the second quarter. Jadran scored three goals in a row for a 5:4 lead in the third period. Before the last quarter, they were a step ahead too (7:6). Marko Petkovic led the hosts to a new two-goal lead in the middle of the last period (8:6). It was a crucial goal because the guests weren&rsquo;t able to recover again. Camarasa netted for 8:7 (03:33), but Radovic&rsquo;s goal in the last minute decided everything and Jadran secured its place in the Preliminary Round.</p>\n\n<p>OSC is the only one that didn&rsquo;t leave the decision for the second match. The Hungarians had defeated Spartak 14:7 in the match in Volgograd, so they had an easy task today. They did a clean job again, winning 12:7. The leaders of the home team were two Serbs, who came from Brescia this summer, Sava Randjelovic (3 goals) and Nemanja Ubovic (2).</p>\n\n<p>Games of the first round of the Preliminary Competition in the Champions League will be played on next Wednesday.</p>\n\n<p>Spartak, Sintez, Red Star and Marseille will play in the Euro Cup quarterfinals.</p>\n\n<h2>2017/18 CHAMPIONS LEAGUE, QUALIFICATION ROUND 3, SECOND LEG</h2>\n\n <h6 >SINTEZ KAZAN 8:7 AN BRESCIA<br />\n(0:2, 0:2, 4:2, 4:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Sintez Kazan (Russia): Odintsov 2, Marzouki 2, Bugaychuk, Klikova, Fatahudintov, Zakirov.<br />\nAN Brescia (Italy): Rizzo 3, Janovic 2, Paskovic, Bertoli.</p>\n\n<p><em>1st leg:7:9, aggregate: 15:16</em></p>\n\n <h6 >JADRAN HERCEG NOVI 9:7 CN MARSEILLE<br />\n(2:1, 2:3, 3:2, 2:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Jadran Carine Herceg Novi (Montenegro): Merkulov 3, Ukropina 2, Petkovic 2, Radovic, Drarskovic.<br />\nCN Marseille (France): I.Kovacevic 2, A. Vukicevic 2, Djurdjic, Camarasa, Kremers &ndash; Taylor.</p>\n\n<p><em>1st leg 7:6. Aggregate: 16:13</em></p>\n\n <h6 >OSC BUDAPEST 12:7 SPARTAK VOLGOGRAD<br />\n(4:2, 1:0, 4:3, 3:2)</h6>\n\n<p>OSC Budapest (Hungary): Randjelovic 3, Ubovic 2, Hegedus 2, Dr. Brguljan 2, Kovacs 2,Kolozsi, Szabo, Juhasz.<br />\nSpartak Volgograd (Russia): Khalturin 3, Ashaev 2, Shaikhutdinov, Kiselev.</p>\n\n<p><em>1st leg: 14:7. Aggregate: 26:14</em></p>\n\n <h6 >CN SABADELL 11:8 CRVENA ZVEZDA<br />\n(2:2, 3:2, 4:1, 2:3)</h6>\n\n<p>CN Sabadell (Spain): Lopez Escribano Jara 3, Fenoy Valverde 2, Cabanas Pegado 2, Carillo Gemar, Gorria Puga, Bustos Sanchez, Muller.<br />\nCrvena zvezda: Tanaskovic 2, Stojanovic 2, Njegovan, Ilic, M. Tadovic, Tankosic.</p>\n\n<p><em>1st match: 6:6. Aggregate: 17:14</em></p>\n\n<h2>PRELIMINARY ROUND</h2>\n\n<p>Group A</p>\n\n<p>Jug (Croatia)<br />\nOlympiacos (Greece)<br />\nBarceloneta (Spain)<br />\nPartizan (Serbia)<br />\nDynamo Moskow (Russia)<br />\nWaspo 89 Hannover (Germany)<br />\nOSC Budapest (Hungary)<br />\nAN Brescia (Italy)</p>\n\n<p>Group B</p>\n\n<p>Szolnok (Hungary)<br />\nPro Recco (Italy)<br />\nSpandau 04 (Germany)<br />\nZF Eger (Hungary)<br />\nAZC Alphen (The Netherlands)<br />\nSteaua Bucharest (Romania)<br />\nJadran Herceg Novi (Montenegro)<br />\nCN Sabadell (Spain)</p>\n\n<h2>EURO CUP</h2>\n\n<p>Spartak Volgograd (Russia), Crvena Zvezda (Serbia), Sintez Kazan (Russia) and Marseille (France) will be paired in quarterfinals of the Euro Cup with Ferencvaros (Hungary), Sport Management (Italy), Miskolc (Hungary) and Jadran Split (Croatia).</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(60, 'Uruguay Takes Water Polo Development Trophy Title', '', '2017-10-24', '<p><img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://swimmingworld.azureedge.net/news/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/generic-water-polo-fina-world-championships-e1465399403957-720x500.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>Uruguay was awarded the FINA World Men&rsquo;s Water Polo Development Trophy title on Sunday October 22 in Gzira, Malta, after the host country team and 2015 Trophy champions Iran were disqualified for unacceptable behaviour within the field of play.</p>\n\n <p>As Malta-Iran were competing in the pool for the gold medal, tensions started to erupt in and out of the water which led to the disqualification of both teams in accordance with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/2017_2021_wp_rules_06102017_new.pdf\"  target=\"_blank\">FINA Water Polo rules</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Following this unfortunate event, Uruguay won the title, followed by Saudi Arabia (silver) and Austria. (bronze).</p>\n\n<p>Santiago San Martin of Uruguay was named as Most Valuable Player of the competition. Diego Villar (PER) was the top scorer, while Alfonso Rodriguez (URU) was the best goalkeeper.</p>\n\n<p>The final ranking of the 2017 Development Trophy is as follows:<br />\n<br />\n<strong>1. Uruguay, 2. Saudi Arabia, 3. Austria,&nbsp;</strong>4. Tunisia, 5. Peru, 6. Singapore</p>\n\n<p>The last edition back in 2015 in Tehran (IRI) was won by the host country team, while Uruguay took silver and Austria bronze. Uzbekistan won the 2013 edition of the Development Trophy in Kuwait City, Egypt and Saudi Arabia came second and third respectively.</p>\n\n<p><em>Press release courtesy of FINA.&nbsp;</em></p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(61, 'Sad end for a great tournament: after disqualifications, Uruguay finishes first', '', '2017-10-24', '<p><img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/styles/top_news/public/top-image/img_6222.jpg?itok=OxKY_3R9\" /></p>\n', '<p>Gergely Csurka, FINA Media Committee</p>\n\n<p><strong>When the coach of Uruguay was tossed to the pool by his players, no one would have guessed that this actually happened to the trophy-winning team&#39;s boss. That time, at the end of the bronze medal match, it was just a great sign of the special value of this tournament. Because it has a special value for those teams who take part.</strong></p>\n\n<p>That was also brilliantly highlighted by the triumphing yells of the Peruvian players while walking in the corridor of the locker-rooms &ndash; they had clinched the 7<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;place in a thriller against Singapore. Or by the height of the jumps of the Austrians at their bench at the very moment when their fifth shooter buried the decisive penalty in the shootout against Tunisia which earned them the 5<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;place (as it turned out to be a win earning them the bronze medal). Or by the joy of the Uruguayans who simply threw their coach to the pool &ndash; usually it happens after the finals of water polo tournaments, here the feeling of claiming the bronze medal sent them to the seventh heaven, and their coach to the water.</p>\n\n<p>However, it turned out later that this had happened to the coach of the team finally being awarded the gold medal.</p>\n\n<p>It was all about tensions which erupted towards the end of the final between Malta and Iran. Malta led 8-6, the last goal came 44 seconds from time and decided the outcome... Eleven seconds later players started provocating each other &ndash; who told what, who began the whole... that part of the story might never be recovered in full. Red cards were shown for two Maltese and five Iranian players but those who had been exlcuded earlier began a mainly verbal fight outside the pool. While the coaches tried to order their players to refrain from making further insults on each other, witnessing the dry-land happenings first the complete Iranian team left the pool and rushed towards the scene then the Maltese players also came out from the water to defend their mates. There were no punches or serious physical violence, the participants just yelled on each other amidst some pushing. Anyway, that should not be part of any water polo games which are supposed to be decided in the pool and not out of it.</p>\n\n<p>The referees had to cancel the match 33 seconds from time and the FINA Technical Water Polo Committee&#39;s Commission couldn&#39;t do anything else than applying the relevant rule which sanctions disciplinary matters in case more than three members of a team commit serious misconduct during a game. (See the decision in the match report.) That meant that both finalists had been disqualified and Uruguay was awarded the trophy.</p>\n\n<p>In fact, they clinched the gold with ease &ndash; as the bronze medal game was the only one-sided encounter of the last session. Uruguay took a commanding lead in the first period and they managed to maintain this 3-4 goals margin until the middle of the last period: there the Saudis had one last surge but after 5-7 the Latin Americans scored a demoralising goal which was followed by three more to secure the bronze medal for them.</p>\n\n<p>The matches for the lower placements produced some extra excitements as both ended in a penalty-shootout. Austria and Tunisia were entangled into battle being full with ups and downs. The last period saw some great twists, the Austrians went 6-8 ahead, the Africans replied with three connecting hits, then a lucky goal helped the European side to go even once more. The last minute saw a goal apiece, the Austrians equalised 28 seconds from time, then their goalie came up with three saves in the shootout.</p>\n\n<p>Peru managed to come back from 2-5 down in the second period and from 6-8 down in the fourth against Singapore to force the shootout. They shut out the Asians in the entire last quarter while netting two goals &ndash; here one save was enough to make the difference and it came from the Peruvian keeper.</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Though, to finish this story in the spirit of sport, we have to add that after an hour or so, the Iranian players reappeared the scene, walked to the Maltese players and shook hands with them &ndash; both teams seemed to close down this unncessary chapter in the only way acceptable. Too bad that peace came far later then it should have.</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/styles/body_1382/public/img_6248.jpg?itok=WDLIxBPY\" /></p>\n\n<p><em>&nbsp;A rare scene: all medallists in one picture &ndash; a kind of happy ending</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>The final rankings of the FINA World Men&rsquo;s Water Polo Development Trophy is as follows:</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. Uruguay</p>\n\n<p>2. Saudi Arabia</p>\n\n<p>3. Austria</p>\n\n<p>4. Tunisia</p>\n\n<p>5. Peru</p>\n\n<p>6. Singapore</p>\n\n<p><em>Malta and Iran have been disqualified.</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.fina.org/sites/default/files/styles/body_1382/public/img_6213.jpg?itok=bppLLxI0\" /></p>\n\n<p><em>MVP of the tournament: Santiago San Martin of Uruguay with FINA TWPC Member Alan Balfanbayev</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>Individual awards</strong></p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Top scorer</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Diego Villar (Peru) with 19 goals</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Most Valuable Player</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Santiago San Martin (Uruguay)</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Best goalkeeper</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Alfonso Rodriguez (Urugay)</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(62, 'The Serbian Champion on Wednesday enters the new season of the strongest competition.', '', '2017-10-25', '<p><img alt=\"Filip Radojevi?\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"http://static.mondo.rs/Picture/664300/jpeg/Filip-Radojevic-vaterpolista-Partizan\" /></p>\n', '<p>Black and white European autumn starts this match at Banjica, match against Partizani against Hungary&#39;s Orshsegetema at 5.30 pm.</p>\n\n<p>The new, youngest team of the most crooked Serbian club will be presented for the first time on the European scene after another major changeover. The club from Banjica has changed from the roots again the team that won the championship title last season.</p>\n\n<p><br />\nNikola Jak&scaron;i? (Ferencvaros), Radomir Dra&scaron;ovi? (Verona), Ognjen Stojanovic, Djordje Tanaskovic, Lazar Dobojanov, Neboj&scaron;a Toholj (all in Zagreb), Mihajlo Repanovic and Petar Velki? (both in &Scaron;abac). came to Dimitrije Risti?evi? (Marseille), Nikola Radonji? (Primorac), Sr?an Aksentijevi?.<br />\nClub secretary Mirko Bradajic said that black and white is expected to be an important season for gaining experience, but that the result will not be in the second plan.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;The team is exceptionally young, but we have had a lot of return with Srdjan Aksentijevic and goalkeeper Dimitar Risticic, with two more experienced players and young beginners getting on the safe side.From tomorrow&#39;s game I expect the players to do their best I do not doubt that will provide 110% he said.</p>\n\n<p>Except for Risti?evi? (1992) and Aksentijevi? (1986), the average age of black and white is about 19 years.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;In the season we have entered with the youngest team in the history of Partizan, so every match with a strong rival, like O&Scaron;C, is a great preparation for us for the upcoming season,&quot; said Stefan ?iri?, head of black and white.</p>\n\n<p>The renowned opponent from Hungary has two representatives of Serbia, Sava Ran?elovi? and Nemanja Ubovi?. There is also Montenegrin Dra&scaron;ko Brguljan, as well as several Hungarian members of the &quot;A&quot; selection.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;O&Scaron;C is a team that has been placed in the final of the Champions League, and I think we can enter into an equal battle with them and try to win a point, so why not three. The difference between the two teams is big but I think that difference we can compensate for the effort and if we impose our rhythm, O&Scaron;C has excellent players in all positions, they have strong spells and no team will easily come to an end, but we do not give up, &quot;said Aksentijevi?.</p>\n\n<p>Partizan is waiting for the first leg of the Champions League almost complete, as only Filip Radojevic will be absent. Tickets for the match are sold at the Banjica cash register, with a stake of 350 dinars for the stands and 700 for the parter.</p>\n\n<p>In the other matches of the first round of the A Group of Champions League play: Dinamo Moscow - South, Vaspo Hanover - Breza and Barseloneta - Olimpijakos.</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(63, 'WATER POLO CHAMPIONS LEAGUE MAIN ROUND, DAY 1 PREVIEW', '', '2017-10-25', '<p><img alt=\"Water Polo Champions League Main Round, Day 1 Preview\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://cdn.swimswam.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Water-Polo-Stock-by-Mike-Lewis-SYD_9266-1082x720.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p><em>Press Release courtesy of LEN</em></p>\n\n<p>For the first time, eight venues will witness Champions League action on one day: the expanded edition of the world&rsquo;s premium water polo competition kicks off on Wednesday with a series of brilliant battles in sight.</p>\n\n<p>After the tremendous success gained in the previous four years, LEN opted to expand the water polo Champions League group stage, from 12 teams to 16.</p>\n\n<p>Granting wild cards for the top clubs of nations with great water polo traditions, Champions League action will reach unchartered waters. Russia, the Netherlands, Romania are on the newcomers&rsquo; list, while Montenegro will re-appear on the big stage after one-year absence. For the first time Spain will have two sides on the battlefield, just as Italy and Germany, while Serbia, Greece and Croatia backs its respective top club to advance to the Final Eight (replacing the Final Six format).</p>\n\n<p>As in the last two seasons, Hungary tops this list with three participants, thanks to the special conditions granted for team sports in the land of the Magyars, which make it possible for them to have three pretty strong squads fighting for the F8 berths with great chances.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Group A</strong></p>\n\n<p>Based on the line-ups&rsquo; strength, 2016 winner and last season&rsquo;s runner-up Jug (CRO) and 2016 silver medallist Olympiacos (GRE) stand out in this group. Barceloneta (ESP), champion in 2014, will try to return to the F8 after they missed the cut last spring for the first time in four years &ndash; which means that the Game of the Day is the Spaniards&rsquo; clash with Olympiacos. Two years ago they met in the prelims, tied in Barcelona (7-7), while the Greeks won at home (9-5).</p>\n\n<p>The race for the top four places will surely include Brescia (ITA), which made the F6 last season just ahead of OSC (HUN) and Hannover might also have a say so its opening match at home against the Italians promises some exciting moments.</p>\n\n<p>Partizan (SRB) always faces the same challenge, to keep the most talented players as long as possible before they join other European clubs, thus the Serbs are not considered real favourites at club level (unlike amongst the national teams) &ndash; still, their youngsters have never offered easy matches to any visiting teams in the still fearful Banica pool. OSC, attempting to make the finals after two failed campaigns, had some experience from the past seasons what it took to survive in Belgrade. Back in 2015-16 they lost the away clash 5-4 and the home clash wasn&rsquo;t an easy cruise either (10-8). Now a first-round appearance in Serbia might require double efforts from the Hungarians in order not to lose valuable points right at the beginning.</p>\n\n<p>The draw could have been more merciful to Dinamo Moscow (RUS), the newcomers have to play with hot favourite Jug on the opening day, perhaps any other rival would have meant an easier task for the Russians.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Group B</strong></p>\n\n<p>The three regular Final Six participants from the past seasons, Recco (ITA) and the two Hungarians, Szolnok and Eger are the front-runners in this group (in fact Recco has a guaranteed berth as the host of next June&rsquo;s Final Eight, though the Italian giant would most probably make the cut on its own). Returner Jadran (MNE), traditional group stage participant Spandau (GER) and the three rookies, Alphen (NED), Steaua (ROU) and Sabadell (ESP) will surely stage fierce battles to clinch the fourth spot.</p>\n\n<p>Title-holder Szolnok and 2015 winner Pro Recco are perhaps out of reach for most of the sides, but Eger had to be cautious while meeting the upcoming teams. Their first visit is already a curious one: in Bucharest, Steaua and its fans will surely try to upset the Hungarians in the Romanians&rsquo; first-ever Champions League match. The same applies to Sabadell where Szolnok&rsquo;s newly shaped team will have its first big encounter of the season.</p>\n\n<p>The clash of Jadran and Spandau will offer thrills as both sides can eye some better ranks this season &ndash; two years ago nothing separated them as both of their matched ended in a 9-9 draw. Perhaps Alphen is the team which faces something we can call &lsquo;mission impossible&rsquo; since the Dutch debut in Recco where no team was able to win a match in the past three years.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Champions League, Preliminaries, Day 1</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong><em>(all times are local)</em></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Group A</strong></p>\n\n<p>19.15 Dynamo Moscow (RUS) v Jug Croatia Osiguranje Dubrovnik (CRO)</p>\n\n<p>19.30 CN Atletic Barceloneta (ESP) v Olympiacos Piraeus (GRE)</p>\n\n<p>19.30 Waspo 98 Hannover (GER) v AN Brescia (ITA)</p>\n\n<p>19.30 Partizan Belgrade (SRB) v A Hid-OSC Budapest (HUN)</p>\n\n<p><strong>Group B</strong></p>\n\n<p>18.15 CN Sabadell (ESP) v Szolnoki Dozsa-Kozgep (HUN)</p>\n\n<p>20.30 Steaua Bucharest (ROU) v ZF Eger (HUN)</p>\n\n<p>20.30 Jadran Herceg Novi (MNE) v Spandau 04 Berlin (GER)</p>\n\n<p>20.30 Pro Recco (ITA) v AZC Alphen (NED)</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(64, 'Hannover mempermalukan Brescia, Jug kalah di Moskow, Recco dan Szolnok menang telak!', '', '2017-10-26', '<p><img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Prlain.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>Hari pertama dari 2017/18 polo air Liga Champions membawa banyak kesenangan dan beberapa permainan yang menegangkan. Sebagian besar favorit meraih kemenangan, tapi ada kejutan besar juga. Hanya tiga tim yang berhasil mengalahkan rival mereka. Semua poin untuk tim tamu mengumpulkan klub Hungaria Szolnok, Eger dan OSC.</p>\n\n<p>KELOMPOK A<br />\nKejutan hari itu terlihat di Jerman, di mana Waspo Hannover mengalahkan Brescia, wakil juara Italia. Jerman menghasilkan keunggulan&nbsp;3: 0 pada kuarter pertama. Brescia tidak bankgit sampai akhir kuarter ketiga saat Rizzo mencetak gol untuk 4: 5. pemain Italia mencoba mengejar dari ketertinggalanya oleh&nbsp;tuan rumah dua kali dalam periode terakhir (5: 6 dan 6: 7). Tapi, Hannover tetap memimpin. Montenegrin Darko Brguljan terjaring untuk skor akhir (8: 6), 02:14 sebelum akhirnya.</p>\n\n<p>Dynamo Moscow absen dari Liga Champions selama lebih dari satu dekade. Dalam pertandingan pertama mereka di CHL setelah 15 tahun, pemain Rusia, diperkuat oleh tiga pemain Serbia (Pijetlovic, Radjen, Subotic), mengalahkan Jug, yang merupakan salah satu favorit untuk gelar tersebut. Orang-orang Kroasia mendominasi babak pertama. Mereka memiliki keunggulan tiga gol (7: 4) 11 detik sebelum turun minum. Jug berusia 8: 5 di menit ke-18. Saat itu diikuti dengan transformasi permainan yang lengkap. Dynamo memotong defisitnya selangkah demi selangkah dan melangkah maju untuk pertama kalinya dua menit dan 15 detik sebelum bel terakhir (11:10). Benic mencetak gol ke-4nya pada malam hari untuk menyamakan kedudukan (11:11), namun Latypov mencetak gol dari angka tambahan (0:25 to go), untuk skor akhir (12:11) dan untuk kesenangan besar pemain Dynamo.</p>\n\n<p>Lain derby Hari 1 di Grup A, dimainkan di Barcelona, ??di mana dua mantan juara Eropa Barceloneta dan Olympiacos berbagi poin. Ada banyak kesulitan dipertandingan tersebut. Olympiakia membuntuti tiga perempat pertama (1: 2, 2: 3, 3: 4), namun orang-orang Yunani memimpin pada pertengahan kuarter keempat. Mereka berada dua langkah di depan Barceloneta, 02:41 menjelang akhir (7: 5). Tuan rumah menyelamatkan poin berkat Perrone dan Larumbe, yang mencapai target di finish dan pertandingan berakhir dengan hasil imbang 7: 7.</p>\n\n<p>OSC Budapest tidak membiarkan kejutan dalam pertandingan melawan Partizan di Beograd, namun pihak Hungaria harus bekerja keras untuk mematahkan perlawanan tim muda dari Belgrade. OSC melompat ke keunggulan 4: 1 di menit ke-6. Tapi, pemain polo air Partizan membuktikan bakat mereka, mereka mulai mendaki kembali dan empat kali mengurangi jarak ke satu (3: 4, 4: 5, 6: 7 dan 7: 8). Partizan gol terakhirnya mencetak gol 5.50 sebelum akhirnya (Radanovic untuk 7: 8). Di sisa pertandingan, Serbia muda kehabisan bensin. OSC, yang dipimpin oleh Balazs Erdely (4 gol) terjaring tiga gol berturut-turut untuk kemenangan 11:07.</p>\n\n<p>KELOMPOK B<br />\nGrup B tidak menawarkan pertandingan yang mendebarkan. Favorit mengalahkan saingan mereka masing-masing dengan mudah.</p>\n\n<p>Pemegang gelar Szolnok menghancurkan pemain polo air Sabadell di Spanyol - 16: 5. Pencetak gol terbanyak adalah dua pemain dari Serbia Andrija Prlainovic dan Milan Aleksic (keduanya Szolnok) dan Gorria (Sabadell), yang masing-masing mencetak 4 gol.</p>\n\n<p>Klub Hungaria lainnya di grup Eger mengalahkan Steaua di Bucharest. Orang-orang Rumania membuntuti 2: 3 pada babak pertama. Tapi, dengan empat gol yang tidak terjawab dari awal babak ketiga hingga pertengahan periode keempat, Eger, yang dipimpin oleh Norbert Hosnyanszki (4 gol) melompat ke keunggulan 7: 2 dan melakukan pelayaran mudah dalam beberapa menit terakhir. Orang Hungaria menang 8:03.</p>\n\n<p>Pemain polo air Carran Jadran melanjutkan barisan permainan dan hasil bagus mereka, yang dimulai pada babak kualifikasi pertama. Mereka menjamu pemain polo air Spandau 04 dan mengalahkan mereka 11: 5. Jerman memimpin 2: 0 di posisi pertama dan 3: 2 sebelum kuarter kedua. Jadran mencetak delapan gol tak terjawab di babak kedua dan di kuarter ketiga dan memastikan kemenangan sebelum masa akhir. Delapan pemain Jadran berhasil memukul target setidaknya satu kali.</p>\n\n<p>Pro Recco menerbangkan pendatang baru dari Belanda, AZC Alphen. Juara Italia memecahkan rekor mencetak gol mereka sendiri dari penyisihan Liga Champions, dari musim lalu (18: 8 melawan Hannover). Mereka mengalahkan saingannya 19: 1. Tim asal Belanda satu-satunya gol terjaring di menit ke-28, setelah 16 gol Recco berturut-turut. Pencetak gol terbanyak dalam pertandingan tersebut adalah kapten Recco Nicolo Figari (4 gol).</p>\n\n<p>2017/18 CHAMPIONS LEAGUE, HARI 1<br />\nGrup A</p>\n\n<p>DINAMO MOSCOW 12:11 JUG DUBROVNIK<br />\n(1: 2, 3: 5, 4: 2, 4: 2)<br />\nDynamo: Nagaev 3, Pijetlovic 2, Latypov 2, Lazarev 2, Radjen, Kholod, Shepelev.<br />\nJug: Benic 4, V. Rasovic 3, Jokovic 2, Ivankovic, Loncar.</p>\n\n<p>WASPO 98 HANNOVER 8: 6 BRESCIA<br />\n(3: 1, 2: 1, 0: 2, 3: 2)<br />\nHannover: Real 2, Da. Brguljan 2, Winkelhorst 2, Bukowski, Radovic.<br />\nBrescia: C. Presciutti 2, Rizzo 2, Nora, N. Presciutti.</p>\n\n<p>PARTIZAN 7:11 OSC BUDAPEST<br />\n(2: 4, 2: 2, 2: 1, 1: 4)<br />\nPartizan: Radanovic, Lazic, Radonjic, F. Jankovic.<br />\nOSC: Erdely 4, Kovacs 2, Randjelovic, Salamon, Toth, Dr. Brguljan, Juhasz.</p>\n\n<p>BARCELONETA 7: 7 OLYMPIACOS<br />\n(1: 1, 2: 1, 1: 1, 3: 4)<br />\nBarceloneta: Mallarach 3, Perrone 2, Fernandez Miranda, Larumbe Gonfaus.<br />\nOlympiakos: Dervisis 2, Mourikis 2, Gounas, Genidounias, Obradovic.</p>\n\n<p>1 OSC Budapest (Hungaria) 1 - 3<br />\n2 Waspo 98 Hannover (Jerman) 1 - 3<br />\n3 Dynamo Moskow (Rusia) 1 - 3</p>\n\n<p>4 Olympacos (Greece) 1 &ndash; 1<br />\n5 Barceloneta (Spain) 1 &ndash; 1<br />\n6 Jug Dubrovnik (Croatia) 1 &ndash; 0<br />\n7 Brescia (Italy) 1 &ndash; 0<br />\n8 Partizan Belgrade (Serbia) 1 &ndash; 0</p>\n\n<p><strong>Group B</strong></p>\n\n <h6 >PRO RECCO 19:1 AZC ALPHEN<br />\n(6:0, 4:0, 5:0, 4:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Pro Recco: Figari 4, Gitto 3, Di Fulvio 3, Mandic 3, Alesiani 2, Aicardi 2, Echenique, Filipovic.<br />\nAlphe: Van Gulik 1.</p>\n\n <h6 >CN SABADELL 5:16 SZOLNOK<br />\n(0:4, 2:5, 2:4, 1:3)</h6>\n\n<p>Sabadell: Bustos Sanchez 4, Canabas 1.<br />\nSzolnok: Prlainovic 4, Aleksic 4, Batori 3, Zalnaki, Jansik, Mezei, Younger, Mi. Cuk.</p>\n\n <h6 >STEAUA BUCHAREST 3:8 ZF EGER<br />\n(1:1, 1:2, 0:2, 1:3)</h6>\n\n<p>Steaua: Dj. Filipovic, Delgado, Murisic.<br />\nEger: Hosnzanszky 4, Vlachopoulos 2, Avramovic, Cuckovic.</p>\n\n <h6 >JADRAN CARINE 11:5 SPANDAU 04<br />\n(2:3, 3:0, 5:0, 1:2)</h6>\n\n<p>Jadran: Merkulov 2, M. Petkovic 2, Krijestorac, B. Banicevic, Dj. Radovic, Spaic, Draskovic<br />\nSpandau 04: Dedovic 2, Gielen 2, Juengling.</p>\n\n<p>1 Pro Recco (Italy) 1 &ndash; 3<br />\n2 Szolnok VSK (Hungary) 1 &ndash; 3<br />\n3 Jadran Carine Herceg Novi (Montenegro) 1 &ndash; 3<br />\n4 ZF Eger (Hungary) 1 &ndash; 3<br />\n5 Steaua Bucharest (Romania) 1 &ndash; 0<br />\n6 Spandau 04 Berlin (Germany) 1 &ndash; 0<br />\n7 Sabadell (Spain) 1 &ndash; 0<br />\n8 AZC Alphen (The Netherlands) 1 &ndash; 0</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(65, 'Kolam Renang GBK Segera Dapat Sertifikat Standar Dunia dari FINA', '', '2017-10-28', '<p><img alt=\"Kolam Renang GBK Segera Dapat Sertifikat Standar Dunia dari FINA\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://cdn.tmpo.co/data/2017/10/20/id_656435/656435_720.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p><span >TEMPO CO</span>,&nbsp;<span >Jakarta</span>&nbsp -&nbsp;Kolam&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.tempo.co/tag/renang&sa=U&ved=0ahUKEwj5x4eMqJDXAhUITLwKHdvXBvkQFggEMAA&client=internal-uds-cse&cx=017919681120236631753:x1vdggjnsq8&usg=AOvVaw1WBEktomHoAMUSgyFnsTE2\" >renang</a>&nbsp Gelora Bung Karno Jakarta atau&nbsp;<span >venue</span>&nbsp;Akuatik GBK mendapat kunjungan dari Federasi Akuatik Dunia atau FINA. Tim FINA, yang diwakili surveyor bernama Pujol Architectura, meninjau langsung ke lokasi pada Jumat pagi, 27 Oktober 2017.</p>\n\n <p>Tim FINA didampingi perwakilan Indonesia, yakni manajer&nbsp;<span >venue</span>&nbsp;dari Persatuan Renang Seluruh Indonesia (PRSI), Wisnu Wardana, dan pemimpin proyek renovasi Akuatik GBK, Anggoro Putro.</p>\n\n<p>Kolam diperiksa selama beberapa jam, mulai panjang dan lebarnya hingga beberapa aspek lain, seperti kolam renang, kolam polo air, dan kolam loncat indah.</p>\n\n <p>Peninjauan tersebut diakhiri dengan penandatanganan rekomendasi yang menunjukkan&nbsp;<span >venue</span>&nbsp;akuatik di GBK sudah sesuai dengan regulasi FINA dan bisa digunakan untuk Asian Games 2018 atau sudah layak mendapatkan sertifikasi.</p>\n\n <div id=\"inarticle\" >\n <div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/14056285/tempo.co/desktop_sport_inarticle_0__container__\" >&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>Hal ini disambut gembira oleh Wisnu, yang juga Ketua Bidang Bina Prestasi PRSI.</p>\n\n <p>&quot;Tujuan kedatangan mereka untuk memberikan hasil yang detail dan lengkap ke FINA dalam segala aspek yang menyangkut&nbsp;<span >venue</span>&nbsp;akuatik,&quot; kata Wisnu, seperti termuat dalam rilis PRSI. &quot;Kami berharap ini bisa disertifikasi dan disetujui FINA&nbsp;sebagai badan sertifikasi tertinggi untuk fasilitas Asian Games.&quot;</p>\n\n<p>Menurut dia, setelah sertifikasi, pihaknya masih akan menyelesaikan beberapa detail kecil dari sisi nonteknis. &quot;Tapi yang kami tekankan dari pihak PRSI adalah kolam ini sudah disertifikasi dan disetujui oleh FINA dan akan keluar hasil sertifikasinya dalam waktu dekat,&quot; ujarnya.</p>\n\n <p>Setelah disertifikasi, arena itu akan dipakai&nbsp;<span >test event</span>&nbsp;cabang&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sport.tempo.co/read/907154/asian-games-2018-atlet-renang-butuh-banyak-uji-coba-luar-negeri\" >renang</a>&nbsp;Asian Games&nbsp;2018 pada 5-15 Desember 2017. &quot;Ini pemeriksaan lanjutan. Sebelumnya sudah dicek pada 26 September lalu. Dan hasilnya bagus, progresnya sudah 99,8 persen dan 6 November bisa finis,&quot; ucap Anggoro.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(66, 'SATLAK PRIMA bubar, Pelatnas Asian Games 2018 diawasi Kemenpora', '', '2017-10-27', '<p><img alt=\"Satlak Prima Bubar, Pelatnas Asian Games 2018 Diawasi Kemenpora\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://cdn.tmpo.co/data/2017/10/25/id_657503/657503_720.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p><span >TEMPO CO</span>,&nbsp;<span >Jakarta</span>&nbsp - Kementerian Pemuda dan Olahraga bertekad akan mengawasi langsung pemusatan latihan nasional (pelatnas) untuk menghadapi&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sport.tempo.co/read/1025091/presiden-oca-puji-persiapan-asian-games-2018-indonesia\" >Asian Games 2018</a>&nbsp;Jakarta-Palembang yang tinggal hitungan bulan.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;Pelaksanaan pelatnas memang sepenuhnya diberikan kepada induk organisasi masing-masing cabang olahraga setelah Satlak Prima dibubarkan, tapi Kemenpora akan secara langsung mengawasi pelaksanaannya agar prestasi terbaik bisa dicapai,&quot; kata pelaksana tugas Deputi Bidang Peningkatan Prestasi Olahraga Kementerian Pemuda, Yuni Poerwanti, di Jakarta, Rabu, 25 Oktober 2017.</p>\n\n<p>Melalui Peraturan Presiden Nomor 95 Tahun 2017 tentang Peningkatan Prestasi Olahraga, pemerintah resmi membubarkan Satuan Pelaksana Program Indonesia Emas (Satlak Prima). Dengan demikian, pengurus pusat atau pengurus besar cabang olahraga menjadi ujung tombak Pelatnas Asian Games 2018.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;Mereka dituntut lebih mandiri dalam pembinaan atlet menuju puncak. Saat ini semuanya harus fokus karena pasti banyak tantangan yang dihadapi,&quot; kata Yuni.</p>\n\n <div id=\"inarticle\" >\n <div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/14056285/tempo.co/desktop_sport_inarticle_0__container__\" >&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n\n <p>Yuni mengatakan Kementerian bersama dengan PP/PB, KONI, KOI, dan&nbsp;<span >stakeholder</span>&nbsp;olahraga Indonesia lainnya mulai memetakan peluang medali emas Asian Games.</p>\n\n <p>Untuk sementara ada delapan cabang olahraga yang diharapkan meraih medali emas, tapi diperkirakan akan bertambah karena data belum semuanya masuk. Kedelapan cabang itu adalah bulu tangkis dua emas,&nbsp;<span >bridge</span>&nbsp dua emas, kano satu emas, jet ski dua emas,&nbsp;<span >paragliding</span>&nbsp dua emas,&nbsp;<span >wushu</span>&nbsp;satu emas, panjat tebing dan taekwondo, kemudian atletik dan angkat besi.</p>\n\n <p>&quot;Peluang emas ini harus dijaga dan diawasi bersama-sama. Jika kita lengah, berarti kita tidak punya&nbsp;<span >passion</span>, quot; ucap Yuni. Adapun Indonesia berharap masuk sepuluh besar&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sport.tempo.co/read/1025091/presiden-oca-puji-persiapan-asian-games-2018-indonesia\" >Asian Games 2018</a>.</p>\n\n <p><span >ANTARA</span></p>\n\n<p><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(67, 'Ratusan Pelajar Tampil di Kejurda Renang Sumut', '', '2017-10-31', '<p><img alt=\"Wagubsu, Nurhajizah Marpaung menemui peserta setelah berenang\" src=\"http://analisadaily.com/assets/image/news/uploader/2017/10/pelajar2.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>Senin, 30 Oktober 2017 | 13:42</p>\n\n<p><strong>Analisadaily (Medan) -</strong>&nbsp;Ratusan peserta ikut ambil bagian dalam Kejuaraan Daerah Renang Pelajar Sumatera Utara di Kolam Renang Selayang, Medan, 30-31 Oktober 2017.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;Even ini diharapkkan bisa menjalin silaturahmi dan sekaligus menjarin atlet-atlet muda yang andalan Sumut di kejuaraan lain baik nasional maupun internasional,&quot; kata Wagubsu, Nurhajizah Marpaung saat membuka acara.</p>\n\n<p>Selain meningkat kebugaran fisik, lanjutnya, olahraga dapat membawa ke arah yang lebih baik yakni tubuh sehat, pikiran dan moral baik. &quot;Serta menghindari dari perbuatan negatif seperti kejahatan dan narkoba,&quot; sebutnya.</p>\n\n<p>Tidak hanya renang, sambungnya, Pemprovsu juga berkomitmen akan terus mendukung demi kemajuan olahraga seperti sepakbola, taekwondo, dan sebagainya. &ldquo;Intinya semua cabor akan terus kami support,&quot; ujarnya.</p>\n\n <p><span >Ketua Panitia, Johan Erik Purba mengatakan, kejuaraan ini diikuti 860 peserta dari 18 kabupaten/kota se-Sumut dan&nbsp;plus Langsa sebagai peserta eksebisi.</span></p>\n\n<p>Antara lain Binjai, Medan, Deli Serdang, Pematang Siantar, Simalungun, Batu Bara, Asahan, Tanjungbalai, Samosir, Sibolga, Tapsel, Padang Sidempuan, Karo, Madina, Labuhanbatu, Taput, Toba Samosir, dan Serdang Bedagai.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;Mereka akan memperebutkan Piala Gubernur serta juara umum akan mendapatkan trofi dan total uang Rp 50 juta,&quot; tuturnya.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(68, 'Croatia and USA the best water polo teams of the year', '', '2017-11-02', '<p><img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Croatia-gold.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>The national teams of Croatia (men) and the USA (women) will be named the best world water polo teams of 2017 by FINA. The federation still hasn&rsquo;t officially announced the decision, but FINA confirmed the criteria of choosing the best teams, on its website.</p>\n\n<p>The criteria are based on the ranking at two major competitions in the season (World Championships and World League). The World Champion earns 180 points, the gold in the World League brings 120 points&hellip;</p>\n\n<p>The list of the nations has been made through a collecting of points earned at the World Championships and in the World League).</p>\n\n <div class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" id=\"attachment_5754\" ><a href=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/USA-women-World-League-gold.jpg\" ><img alt=\"USA women World League gold\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-5754\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/USA-women-World-League-gold-300x200.jpg\"  /></a>\n\n<p>USA women World League gold&nbsp;Photo: insidethegames.biz</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Croatia men team earned 180 points as the World Champion and 80 for the bronze medal in the FINA World League. The Croats have 10 points more than Serbia, that was the World League winner (120 points) and took the 3rd place at the World Championships (130points). Serbia was the best team of the year in 2015 and in 2016</p>\n\n<p>The USA dominates World women water polo for years. The girls from the USA won the gold medals at the World Championships as well as in the World League and they collected all 300 points.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Ranking system criteria</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>World Championships and Olympic Games</strong>: 1st place: 180 points, 2nd place: 140 points, 3rd place: 130 points, 4th place:100 points, 5th place:90 points, 6th place: 80 points&hellip;</p>\n\n<p><strong>FINA World League</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; 1st place: 120 points, 2nd place: 90 points, 3rd place: 80 points, 4th place: 60<br />\npoints, 5h place: 50 points, 6th place: 40 points&hellip;</p>\n\n<p><strong>FINA World Cup (wasn&rsquo;t held this year)</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; 1st place: 80 points, 2nd place: 70 points, 3rd place: 60 points, 4th place: 40 points, 5th place: 35 points, 6th place: 25 points&hellip;</p>\n\n<p>The bests teams and athletes in all disciplines will be officially announced at the FINA World Aquatics Gala &ldquo;The Night of Stars&rdquo; in Sanya City (China) on 2 December.</p>\n\n<h2>THE BEST WORLD WATER POLO TEAMS OF THE YEAR, UNOFFICIAL RANKING</h2>\n\n<p><strong>Men</strong><br />\n1 Croatia 260 points (180 World Championships + 80 World League)<br />\n2 Serbia 250 (130 WCH + 120 WL)<br />\n3 Italy 170 (80 WCH +90 WL)<br />\n4 Hungary 140 (140 WCH + 0 WL)<br />\n5 Greece 125 (100 WCH +25&nbsp; WL)<br />\n6 Russia 110 (60 WCH + 50WL)<br />\n&hellip;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Women</strong></p>\n\n<p>1 USA 300 (180 WCH + 120WL)<br />\n2 Russia 210 (130 WCH + 80WL)<br />\n3 Canada 190(100 WCH + 90 WL)<br />\n4 Hungary 150 (90WCH + 60WL)<br />\n5 Spain 140 (140 WCH + 0 WL)<br />\n&hellip;</p>\n\n<h2>PAST WINNERS</h2>\n\n<p><em>Until 2014, FINA had been choosing the best players. The prizes for the best teams were introduced in 2015.</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>MEN</strong></p>\n\n<p>2010 Vanja Udovicic (Serbia)<br />\n2011 Filip Filipovic (Serbia)<br />\n2012 Josip Pavic (Croatia)<br />\n2013 Denes Varga (Hungary)<br />\n2014 Filip Filipovic (Serbia)<br />\n&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;<br />\n2015 Serbia<br />\n2016 Serbia</p>\n\n<p><strong>WOMEN</strong></p>\n\n<p>2010 ELizabeth Armstrong (USA)<br />\n2011 Alexandra Asimaki (Greece)<br />\n2012 Maggie Steffens (USA)<br />\n2013 Jennifer Pareja (Spain)<br />\n2014 Maggie Steffens (USA)<br />\n&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;<br />\n2015 USA<br />\n2016 USA</p>\n\n<p><strong>Best coaches</strong><br />\n2015 Dejan Savic (Serbia, men) and Adam Krikorian (USA, women)<br />\n2016 Dejan Savic (Serbia, men) and Adam Krikorian (USA, women)</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi');
