(69, 'EUROPE WATER POLOThree Hungarian clubs hunt Super Cup', '', '2017-11-03', '<p><img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/supercup-photo-waterpolo.hu_.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>A series of big water polo finals which have been held in Budapest this year will be ended tomorrow.</p>\n\n<p>The famous &ldquo;Komjadi pool&rdquo;, will be the venue of the European Super Cup finals, both for men and for women. Men&rsquo;s final will see all-Hungarian battle between Szolnok, the champion of Europe, and Ferencvaros, Europe Cup winner. Euro League winner Kinef Kirishi (Russia) and Hungarian UVSE, that won LEN Trophy, will clash in the final for women.</p>\n\n<h2>BUDAPEST SERIES</h2>\n\n<p>Since the start of the season, the capital of Hungary has hosted four major water polo competitions. The series started on April 5th, with the 2nd match of the LEN Euro Cup finals (Ferencvaros and Oradea were tied- 7:7, but the Hungarians celebrated a 12:6 win in Romania). Late in April, UVSE won the first place at the LEN Trophy Final Four.</p>\n\n<p>Szolnok clinched its first title of European champion in the newly built &ldquo;Duna Arena&rdquo;, at the Champions League Final Six (25-27 May). The FINA World Championships was held at the Marget Sziget Island. The Hungarian teams didn&rsquo;t manage to win the titles. Men&rsquo;s team was the 2nd, while women took the 5th place</p>\n\n<h2>DOMESTIC DERBY</h2>\n\n<p>Szolnok has played magnificently this year. It won the national title and the Hungarian Cup and remained unbeaten at the European stage. Szolnok players earned 19 points (9 wins and 1 draw) in the Champions League Preliminary Group. They beat Eger in the semifinals (7:5) and they dominated the final game of the Champions League, defeating 2016 winner Jug (10:5).</p>\n\n<p>The title-holder showed no mercy at the start of this season&rsquo;s Champions League. In the first round, it demolished Sabadell (15:6).</p>\n\n <p><a href=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/supercupfull.jpg\" ><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-7335\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/supercupfull-214x300.jpg\"  /></a>Szolnok will be the favourite tomorrow, but Ferencvaros has a big chance too. After years of absence from big European finals and semifinals, Ferencvaros, the winner of four titles in the discontinued Cup Winner&rsquo;s Cup (seasons 1975, 1978, 1980 and 1998), started the 2016/17 season very ambitiously, by bringing a few important reinforcements. Among them were two former Szolnok players Daniel Varga and Stefan Mitrovic. A few months ago, two more players moved from Szolnok to Ferencvaros&ndash; Denes Varga and Marton Vamos, the MVP of the 2017 World Championships.</p>\n\n<p>Ferencvaros dominates in the first two legs of this season&rsquo;s Euro Cup, it achieved nine victories in nine games.</p>\n\n<p>Both clubs are unbeaten in this season&rsquo;s domestic competitions.</p>\n\n<p>Szolnok competes in the Super Cup for the first time, while Ferencvaros won trophies in 1978 and 1980. But, tradition is on the Szolnok&rsquo;s side. Winner of the Euro Cup (earlier LEN Trophy) has never won the Super Cup.</p>\n\n<h2>TWO DEBUTANTS IN WOMEN&rsquo;S FINAL</h2>\n\n<p>Kinef Kirishi and UVSE are debutants in the LEN Super Cup. Last season, the Russians eventually won their first-ever European trophy after five lost finals. The 2016/17 Euro League Final Four was held in their pool. They defeated Mataro (Spain) in the semifinals (11:8) and beat Olympiacos (Greece) in a thrilling final match (7:6).<br />\nThere were a lot of excitements in the final game of the 2016/17 LEN Trophy, too. UVSE also achieved a close 7-6 win against Padova (Italy). Before that, UVSE beat Dunajvaros in the semifinals (8:6).</p>\n\n<p>The 2017/18 Super Cup will be the third European final in the history of UVSE. They played in the 2015/16 Euro League final when Sabadell defeated them 11:8.</p>\n\n<p>The encounter between UVSE and Kirishi will start at 15.45. The matchSzolnok &ndash;Ferencvaros is scheduled for 18.15.</p>\n\n<h2>PAST WINNERS</h2>\n\n<p><strong>MEN</strong></p>\n\n<p>1976 Mladost (Yugoslavia)<br />\n1977 CSKA Moscow (USSR)<br />\n1978 Ferencvaros (Hungary)<br />\n1979 Orvosegyetem (Hungary)<br />\n1980 Ferencvaros (Hungary)<br />\n1981 CSKA Moscow (USSR)<br />\n1982 Barcelona (Spain)<br />\n1983 CSKA Moscow (USSR)<br />\n1984 POSK (Yugoslavia)<br />\n1985 Vasas (Hungary)<br />\n1986 Spandau 04 (West Germany)<br />\n1987 Spandau 04 (West Germany)<br />\n1988 Pescara (Italy)<br />\n1989 Not held<br />\n1990 Mladost (Yugoslavia)<br />\n1991 Partizan (Yugoslavia)<br />\n1992 Catalunya (Spain)<br />\n1993 Pescara (Italy)<br />\n1994 Ujpest (Hungary)<br />\n1995 Catalunya (Spain)<br />\n1996 Mladost (Croatia)<br />\n1997-2001 Not held<br />\n2002 Olympiacos (Greece)<br />\n2003 Pro Recco (Italy)<br />\n2004 Honved (Hungary)<br />\n2005 Posillipo (Italy)<br />\n2006 Jug (Croatia)<br />\n2007 Pro Recco (Italy)<br />\n2008 Pro Recco (Italy)<br />\n2009 Primorac Kotor (Montenegro)<br />\n2010 Pro Recco (Italy)<br />\n2011 Partizan (Serbia)<br />\n2012 Pro Recco (Italy)<br />\n2013 Crvena zvezda (Serbia)<br />\n2014 Barceloneta (Spain)<br />\n2015 Italy Pro Recco<br />\n2016 Jug (Croatia)<br />\n2017 ?<br />\n<em>From 1976 to 2002, the LEN Super Cup was an encounter between the winners of the Champions Cup /Champions League and a winner of the Cup Winners&rsquo; Cup. Since the discontinuation of the Cup Winners&rsquo; Cup, a European Champion and a winner of the Euro Cup (earlier the LEN Trophy) have been playing in the Super Cup.</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>WOMEN</strong></p>\n\n<p>2006 Honved (Hungary)<br />\n2007 Fiorentina (Italy)<br />\n2008 Orizzonte Catania (Italy)<br />\n2009 Vouliagmeni (Greece)<br />\n2010 Vouliagmeni (Greece)<br />\n2011 Pro Recco (Italy)<br />\n2012 Imperia (Italy)<br />\n2013 Sabadell (Spain)<br />\n2014 Sabadell (Spain)<br />\n2015 Olympiacos (Greece)<br />\n2016 Sabadell (Spain)<br />\n2017 ?</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(70, 'Tim Polo Air Sumsel Taklukkan Sulsel di Indonesia Open Aquatic 2017', '', '2017-12-10', '<p><img alt=\"Tim Polo Air Sumsel Taklukkan Sulsel di Indonesia Open Aquatic 2017\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.gonews.co/assets/news/10122017/gonewsco_ftaxz_34340.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p><strong>PALEMBANG -&nbsp;</strong><span >Test Event Road To Asian Games 2018, bertajuk CIMB Niaga Indonesia Open Aquatic Championship 2017 berjalan semakin seru. Hari ke-6, Minggu (10/12/2017), mempertandingkan cabang Renang dan Polo Air, di GBK Aquatic Stadium.</span></p>\n\n <p><span >Di Polo Air Putri, Tim Polo Air Sumatera Selatan (Sumsel) tampil perkasa saat menghadapi Sulawesi Selatan (Sulsel). Sumsel besutan Anugrah Widi, sanggup menang telak 24-8.</span></p>\n\n <p><span >Kemenangan juga diraih Tim Polo Air Putri Jawa Barat (Jabar) kala melawan Jambi. Ivy Nernie yang mengoleksi 6 gol, dan 5 gol dari Upiet Sarimanah, sanggup memastikan kemenangan untuk Jabar dengan skor akhir 23 melawan 1.</span></p>\n\n <p><span >Dewi Fortuna belum juga berpihak pada Jambi ketika melawan DKI Jakarta. Jambi yang dilatih Mulyadi kebobolan 28 gol, dan hanya sanggup membalas 2 gol.</span><br />\n <span >Dan laga terakhir di hari ini Jawa Barat kontra Sulawesi Selatan. Jabar yang tampil mengesankan berhasil menang telak, 26-1.</span></p>\n\n <p><span >Esok hari, Senin (11/12/2017), akan memainkan partai penyisihan Polo Putri Jawa Barat vs Sumatera Selatan, Sulawesi Selatan vs DKI Jakarta, DKI Jakarta vs Sumatera Selatan, dan Sulawesi Selatan vs Jambi,&nbsp;</span></p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(71, 'Fradi is the boss in Budapest', '', '2018-01-31', '<p><img alt=\"Stefan Mitrovic, water polo player\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/fradi.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>Szolnok and Eger water polo clubs continued to dominate in Hungarian championship, while Honved made a huge step towards top four finish in the B group of the competition.</p>\n\n<p>The defending champion collected one more huge win, this time it was against visiting team of Vasas &ndash; 20:3. The Budapest water polo club is still fighting for the fourth place in the A group of the championship.</p>\n\n<p>Tonight it was a game of cat and mouse in Szolnoki. There is no other way to describe a duel in which the home team leads 9:0 at the halftime. It was Szolnok&rsquo;s tenth consecutive victory against Vasas in Hungarian championship.</p>\n\n<p>Also, this was a third time in the season that Szolnok scored 20 or more goals in a single game. Fulop Bence was the best scorer for the European water polo champion with four goals.</p>\n\n<p>Eger water polo players had an easy task because they played away against the worst team in the league &ndash; Szeged. Of course, they won big &ndash; 16:4 and maintained a perfect record in the B group.</p>\n\n<p>Norbert Dabrowski&rsquo;s men started the game furiously with a 3:0 lead and after that, it was just the question how big goal difference is going to be.</p>\n\n<p>Strahinja Rasovic was definitely a man of the match with five goals, while Uros Cuckovic scored a hattrick for Eger. This was a 12th straight defeat for Szeged water polo team.</p>\n\n<p>Another Budapest team, Honved maintained a course for securing the fourth place in the B group, after a win against visiting Szentes &ndash; 11:6. Honved opened the door to victory in the last minutes of the second quarter when it took a 5:2 lead.</p>\n\n<p>With two more goals and a rock-solid defense in the third period the home team definitely secured an important victory, while Szentesi lost the last chance to enter the fight for the fourth place with this defeat.</p>\n\n<p>In the big Budapest derby, Ferencvaros defeated BVSC 10:7 and saved a theoretical chance to catch Szolnok in the leading place of the A group. Two teams were tied (6:6) at the beginning of the last period of the game.</p>\n\n<p>Marton Vamos opened that period with a goal that gave Fradi a lead and soon after that Jansik Szilard scored to take the home team to 8:6. When Denes Varga found the net three minutes before the end of the game, it was clear that Ferencvaros is going to win another city derby.</p>\n\n<h2>ROUND 12</h2>\n\n<p>Wednesday, January 31</p>\n\n <h6 >SZOLNOK 20:3 VASAS<br />\n(4:0, 5:0, 6:2, 5:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Szolnok: F&uuml;l&ouml;p 4, Jansik 3, Hangay 3, Mezei 3, Younger 3, Zal&aacute;nki 2, Kis, Prlainovic<br />\nVasas: Bencz, Buri&aacute;n, Steinmetz</p>\n\n <h6 >SZEGED 4:16 EGER<br />\n(0:3, 2:3, 1:4, 1:6)</h6>\n\n<p>Szeged: Irmes 2, Szilvas&aacute;n, B&ouml;rcs&ouml;k<br />\nEger: S. Rasovic 5, Cuckovic 3, Hosny&aacute;nszky 2, Avramovic 2, Decker, Kov&aacute;cs, Magyar, Vlachopoulos</p>\n\n <h6 >FERENCVAROS 10:7 BVSC<br />\n(2:2, 2:3, 2:1, 4:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Ferencvaros: S. Mitrovic 3, De. Varga 2, Jansik, V&aacute;mos, Da. Varga, Madaras, Jaksic<br />\nBVSC: P&aacute;sztor 3, Kov&aacute;cs, M&eacute;sz&aacute;ros, Szab&oacute; Bence, Szab&oacute; Bendeg&uacute;z</p>\n\n <h6 >PVSK 6:4 TATABANYA<br />\n(1:1, 3:0, 1:1, 1:2)</h6>\n\n<p>PVSK: Csacsovszky 3, Csaba, Lajk&oacute;, Rakonjac<br />\nTatabanya: Hopp&aacute;l, Szab&oacute;, Szentesi, Kolarik</p>\n\n <h6 >HONVED 11:6 SZENTES<br />\n(2:2, 3:0, 2:0, 4:4)</h6>\n\n<p>Honved: Sziv&oacute;s 3, Simon 2, Vad 2, Ill&eacute;s, Gy&aacute;rf&aacute;s, Irmes, Balakirjev<br />\nSzentes: Somogyi 2, Nagy, Pellei, V&ouml;r&ouml;s, T&oacute;th</p>\n\n <h6 >KAPOSVAR 11:6 DOMINO AVUS<br />\n(3:0, 4:1, 3:4, 1:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Kaposvar: Vindisch 2, Varga 2, Kov&aacute;cs 2, Pataki 2, T&oacute;th, Luk&aacute;cs, Palot&aacute;s<br />\nDomino Avus: Ekler 2, Basara 2, Garancsy, Baj</p>\n\n <h6 >OSC 8:4 MISKOLC<br />\n(3:1, 1:1, 2:2, 2:0)</h6>\n\n<p>OSC: Erdelyi 2, Seman 2, Bundschuh, Kovacs, Brguljan, Randjelovic<br />\nMiskolc: Nagy 2, Berta, Vadovics</p>\n\n <h6 >DEBRECEN 13:5 UVSE<br />\n(2:0, 3:3, 5:1, 3:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Debrecen: K&aacute;llay 3, Gyurik 3, Boros 2, Vidovics 2, Fej?s, Fekete, Obradovic<br />\nUVSE: Major, R&aacute;bav&ouml;lgyi, Kor&eacute;nyi, N&eacute;meth, Dala</p>\n\n<h2>STANDINGS</h2>\n\n<h2>GROUP A</h2>\n\n<p>1. Szolnok 12 games -36 pts<br />\n2. FTC 12 &ndash; 33,<br />\n3. BVSC 12 &ndash; 22,<br />\n4. Vasas 12 &ndash; 15,<br />\n5. Debrecen 12 &ndash; 13,<br />\n6. Kaposv&aacute;r 12 &ndash; 12,<br />\n7. AVUS 12 &ndash; 6,<br />\n8. UVSE 12 &ndash; 4</p>\n\n<h2>GROUP B</h2>\n\n<p>1. Eger 11 &ndash; 33<br />\n2. OSC 12 &ndash; 30<br />\n3. Miskolc 12 &ndash; 22<br />\n4. Honv&eacute;d 12 &ndash; 19<br />\n5. P&eacute;cs 12 &ndash; 16,<br />\n6. Tatab&aacute;nya 11 &ndash; 10,<br />\n7. Szentes 12 &ndash; 9<br />\n8. Szeged 12 &ndash; 0</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(72, 'Let\'s Join', '', '2018-02-08', '<p><img alt=\"Image may contain: 7 people, people smiling, text\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://scontent-sit4-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/27459967_1995990580430665_4024316435971871086_n.jpg?oh=662cbbba5f47132936a0837c09517cb9&oe=5B1E0816\" /></p>\n', '<p><span >Let&#39;s Join !!&nbsp;</span><br />\n<br />\n <span >ayo..ajak putra putri anda untuk bergabung bersama klub Tirta Sriwijaya Aquatic, terutama bagi yang sudah bisa berenang dan ingin menjadi atlit yang handal dan dilatih oleh pelatih yang berpengalaman.</span><br />\n<br />\n <a href=\"http://www.smswaterpolo.club/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"  target=\"_blank\">www.smswaterpolo.club</a><br />\n <span >email : tsac@smswaterpolo.club</span></p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(73, 'Mou antara Tirta Sriwijaya Aquatic Club dengan Sekolah Islam Al-Azhar Cairo Palembang', '', '2018-02-26', '<p><img alt=\"Image may contain: 4 people, people smiling, people standing\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://scontent-sin6-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/28168373_2017424184953971_375225748065285062_n.jpg?oh=147a34d7f13222d25b175be652e19e46&oe=5B102F1B\" /></p>\n', '<p>MoU antara Sekolah Islam Al-Azhar Cairo Palembang dengan klub Tirta Sriwijaya Aquatic dalam melaksanakan kegiatan ekstrakulikuler disekolah tersebut sekaligu juga untuk mempermudah pencarian bibit atlit renang dan polo air kota Palembang dan Provinsi Sumatera Selatan.</p>\n\n<p>semoga dengan terjalinnya kerjasama tersebut dapat bermanfaat bagi orang yang terlibat didalamnya.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nbagi orangtua murid yang belum mendaftarkan putra-putri nya&nbsp;&nbsp;ayo segera mendaftarkan putra dan putri anda ke Klub TSAC<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(76, '15-player teams at 33rd European Championships?', '', '2018-03-16', '<p><img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/barcelona2018.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>Beberapa Proposal tentang &nbsp;peraturan polo air baru telah menjadi topik yang sangat hangat dalam 10-12 bulan terakhir.</p>\n\n<p>Hanya satu dari proposal yang diadopsi pada 2017. Komite Olimpiade Internasional menyetujui untuk menggunakan&nbsp; 11 pemain dalam sebuah tim yang akan ikut bertanding.</p>\n\n<p>Di sisi lain, European Aquatics Federation (LEN) telah mempersiapkan perubahan untuk kompetisi. Komite Polo Air Teknis LEN (TWPC) telah membuat proposal pada pertemuan di Barcelona. Diharapkan Biro LEN akan menerima proposal ini pada konvensi yang akan diadakan akhir pekan depan.</p>\n\n<p>Perubahan terbesar yang terjadi adalah jumlah pemain yang lebih besar dalam tim di kompetisi LEN, yang sama sekali berlawanan dengan perubahan IOC.</p>\n\n<p>Jika LEN Bureau menerima proposal tersebut, setiap tim akan mendaftarkan 15 pemain untuk Kejuaraan Eropa ke-33 di Barcelona (14-28 Juli). Pelatih akan mengantarkan daftar 13 pemain dua jam sebelum masing-masing pertandingan. Mereka akan bisa mengubah tim untuk setiap pertemuan.</p>\n\n<p>Aturan ini akan diadopsi untuk semua kompetisi LEN dari musim depan.</p>\n\n<p>Sistem kualifikasi untuk kompetisi LEN baru Piala Europa akan diubah.</p>\n\n<p>Seperti di tahun ini, Delapan Besar untuk pria dan Enam Final untuk wanita akan dipentaskan di musim depan. Jika Biro LEN mengadopsi perubahan, dalam kompetisi awal 16 tim pria akan dibagi menjadi empat kelompok, sementara 12 regu wanita akan ditarik ke dalam tiga kelompok. Keenam tim pria dan enam terbaik wanita terbaik di Kejuaraan Eropa 2018 akan secara langsung memenuhi syarat untuk persiapan. Semua tim lain akan memainkan kualifikasi untuk tahap awal.</p>\n\n<p>MELALUI EUROPA CUP TERHADAP PIALA CHAMPION&nbsp;DAN SUPER LEAGUE FINAL?<br />\n<br />\nDengan proposal tersebut, di&nbsp;Kejuaraan Eropa yang akan datang yaitu 2019 dan 2021, Piala Europa akan menjadi bagian dari sistem kualifikasi untuk ECH. Sebagai contoh, empat pemain terbaik dan tiga tim putri terbaik di Piala Eropa, yang tidak akan lolos ke Kejuaraan Eropa 2020 melalui ECH 2018, mengamankan tempat mereka di Kejuaraan Eropa. Komposisi turnamen polo air putra tersebut adalah: 8 tim terbaik dari ECH sebelumnya, 4 dari Piala Eropa&nbsp;dan 4 dari kualifikasi, sementara di turnamen polo air putri tersebut akan bersaing: 6 tim terbaik di Barcelona, ??3 dari piala Europa dan 3 dari kualifikasi</p>\n\n<p>Komite Polo Air Teknis LEN dan FINA telah menyetujui sistem baru kualifikasi Eropa untuk Super Final Liga Dunia. Jika badan pemerintahan kedua federasi tersebut mencapai kesepakatan akhir, keempat pria terbaik dan empat tim wanita terbaik di Piala Europa akan lolos ke Super Final Liga Dunia.(AW)<br />\n<br />\n-waterpology-</p>\n\n<p>www.waterpology.com</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(77, 'EUROPELEN and FINA to discuss 15-player rosters rule', '', '2018-03-19', '<p><img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/golman.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>The LEN Bureau still hasn&rsquo;t approved a new rule of a larger number of players in teams at major competitions, but the question has been opened for discussions between representatives of the international federations.</p>\n\n<p>The LEN Technical Water Polo Committee has proposed a new rule, by which every team would register 15 players for every major multi-day competition. The coaches would deliver a list of 13 players two hours before each match.</p>\n\n<p>This proposal has been one of the topics at the first LEN Bureau meeting in 2018, held in Valetta (Malta).</p>\n\n<p>In today&rsquo;s press release, LEN announced that the Bureau had agreed to further explore the possibilities to have 15-member teams at the big competitions.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;We need to continue discussions with FINA and other continents as we consider this change a benefit for the sport. Water polo players face growing physical demands as the calendar is getting busier. We all hope we can reach a consensus in the future&rdquo;, LEN President Paolo Barelli said (source: LEN press release)</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>LEN hasn&rsquo;t announced anything about the possibility to adopt the 15-player roster rule at the 2018 European Championships in Barcelona.</p>\n\n<p>Some other changes of the LEN water polo competitions have been agreed at the meeting.</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;The Bureau agreed that the new event for national teams, the water polo Europa Cup should be open for all and will qualify four teams to the following edition of the European Championships&rdquo;, LEN announced.</p>\n\n<p>According to this information, at European Championships for men would play the teams ranked 1 &ndash; 8 at the previous championships, 4 from the Europa Cup and 4 from the qualifications. The composition of the women tournaments would be the top six teams at the previous championships, four from the Europa Cup and two from the qualifications.</p>\n\n<p>LEN and FINA representatives negotiate the proposal that the 2019 Europa Cup may be the continental qualifications for the World League Super Finals.</p>\n\n<p>LEN has included the U15 European Championships in the competition calendar. The first championships for 15-years old and younger players will be held in 2019.</p>\n\n<p>One of the decisions of the LEN Bureau has been a growth of prize money for the athletes and for the National Federations at the competitions in 2018. LEN will offer 1,5 million Euros (the highest fund in the history) for awards at major LEN events this year: the European Championships in Glasgow (swimming, synchronised swimming, diving and open water swimming), in Barcelona (water polo), the Europa Cup (water polo), the Champions League (water polo), and other continental competitions in aquatic sports.</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(78, 'FINA WORLD LEAGUEMontenegro knocks Serbia to make a huge step for the Super Final', '', '2018-03-21', '<p><img alt=\"World league\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://www.waterpology.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/mne.jpg\" /></p>\n', '<p>After five gold medals in the World League, Serbian national water polo is unlikely to play this year&rsquo;s final tournament of this competition. In the decisive match of the preliminary phase, Montenegro won against Serbia 11:8 (3: 2, 4: 2, 1: 1, 3: 3) in the newly opened swimming pool in Podgorica.</p>\n\n<p>In the first duel of these two teams Serbia also won by three (7:4) and tonight Dra&scaron;ko Brguljan scored the decisive 11th goal for Montenegro from penalty six seconds before the final whistle.</p>\n\n<p>That win will be enough for the Montenegrins to qualify for the Super Final tournament if they beat Romania away in the last match (April 10) with more than five goals difference.</p>\n\n<p>Serbia is still the first in the group with three points more than Montenegro, but it would be a sensation if Montenegrins do not triumph in that match and confirm the place in the final event of the World League.</p>\n\n<p>Montenegrin water polo players got off the better start of the match and quickly gained three goals advantage (5: 2). In the middle of the match, Montenegrins made a series of three consecutive goals (from 5:4 to 8:4), but Serbia somehow quickly responded and came close to a deficit of two goals (6:8).</p>\n\n<p>In the last quarter, Serbia continued in the same rhythm. Stefan Mitrovic and Gavril Subotic both found the net and after that Montenegro had just one goal lead 9:8.</p>\n\n<p>But then, the home team woke up, Ukropina scored the 10th goal for Montenegro water polo team and Drasko Brguljan gave the much-wanted win with a three-goal difference.<br />\n&ldquo;It is a deserved triumph of Montenegro, now they are close to the final success, but I must say that I think that the penalty did not exist at all in the end, and we are not happy with some referees decisions. About the game I can say that after the first two quarters in which we looked asleep, we played as it should be&rdquo;, said Dusan Mandic of Serbia.</p>\n\n<p>His compatriot Viktor Rasovic added.<br />\n&ldquo;We did not have aggressiveness in the first two quarters, but we started to play in the third quarter. I never talk about the referees but I think they directly damaged our chances to secure a place at the final tournament&rdquo;, said Rasovic.</p>\n\n<p>In the other match of the night, Hungarian water polo team trashed Netherlands 13:1 to take a three-point lead at the top of their World League qualifying group. In the last round of this phase of the competition they play against Spain and after that match the winner of the group will be decided.</p>\n\n<p>What is there to say about a game in which Hungarians had a 9:0 lead after the first three quarters? Lindhout scored the only goal for the visiting team and after the 32 minutes, Erdelyi Balazs was the best scorer with three goals, while Batori Bence, Gergo Zalanki, and Viktor Vadovics each found the net twice.</p>\n\n<h2>WORLD LEAGUE</h2>\n\n<h2>ROUND 5</h2>\n\n<h2>GROUP A</h2>\n\n <h6 >MONTENEGRO 11:8 SERBIA<br />\n(3:2, 4:2, 1:1, 3:3)</h6>\n\n<p>Montenegro: Brguljan 3, Ukropina 3, Ivovic 2, Misic 2, Spaic,<br />\nSerbia: Mandic 2, Lazic 2, S. Mitrovic, Jaksic, V. Rasovic, Subotic</p>\n\n<h2>STANDINGS</h2>\n\n<p>1. Serbia 4 games &ndash; 9pts<br />\n2. Montenegro 3 &ndash; 6<br />\n3. Romania 3 &ndash; 0</p>\n\n<h2>GROUP C</h2>\n\n <h6 >HUNGARY 13:1 NETHERLANDS<br />\n(2:0, 2:0, 5:0, 4:1)</h6>\n\n<p>Hungary: Erd&eacute;lyi 3, Vadovics 2, Zal&aacute;nki 2, B&aacute;tori 2, Mezei, Sedlmayer, Manhercz, Bed?<br />\nNetherlands: Lindhout</p>\n\n<h2>STANDINGS</h2>\n\n<p>1. Hungary 3 &ndash; 9<br />\n2. Spain 3 &ndash; 6<br />\n3. Netherlands 4 &ndash; 0</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(79, 'TIRTA SRIWIJAYA AQUATIC Juara POLO AIR U12 - LISCA TOURNAMENT 2017 Session II di kolam UPH Jakarta', '', '2018-04-28', '<p><img alt=\"Image may contain: 16 people, people smiling, people standing\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://scontent-sit4-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/31369622_2089392831090439_6650407402136928256_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&oh=5410138f970b2405b4188946fc5565e6&oe=5B4FC533\" /></p>\n', '<p>Lisca&nbsp;(League of inter school and collegiate aquatic) yang diselenggarakan tiap tahun&nbsp;di kolam Universitas Pelita Harapan - Tangerang Banten. Untuk pertama kalinya kejuaraan tersebut menyelenggarakan nomor pertandingan polo air mini kategori usia 12 tahun dimana diikuti oleh 6 peserta yang mewakili klub dan daerah.</p>\n\n<p>Tirta Sriwijaya Aquatic keluar sebagai pemenang pada kejuaraan tersebut, pemain andalan klub Amanda Savira berhasil menghantar klub TSAC ke podium juara sekaligus juga menobatkan Amanda Savira sebagai pencetak goal terbanyak pada kejuaraan tersebut.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Image may contain: 7 people, people smiling, people standing\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://scontent-sit4-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/31381253_2089393104423745_2110346444475990016_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&oh=769c52606ec3e96be281b85ae85177be&oe=5B4F6602\" /></p>\n\n<p>Kejuaraan ini merupakan ajang resmi dibawah bidang pembinaan dan pretasi PB PRSI, semoga kedepannya akan lebih banyak lagi kejuaraan serupa baik di daerah maupun di ibukota untuk lokasi pertandingannya.<br />\nTentunya klub Tirta Sriwijaya Aquatic yang baru pertama kali keikut sertaanya pada lisca 2017 session ii ini diharapkan bisa memberikan pengalaman tersendiri bagi anak-anak, pelatih, dan juga orang tua.&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
(84, 'ASCA Certification in Penang-Malaysia', '', '2018-04-29', '<p><img alt=\"Image may contain: 2 people, people smiling, people standing\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://scontent-sin6-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/31437313_2090320167664372_3984856741534760960_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&oh=360723e195c9090e0d02a9e1ff159c75&oe=5B578D4D\" /></p>\n', '<p>selamat kepada para pelatih dari Tirta Sriwijaya Aquatic Club yang telah mendapatkan Sertifikasi ASCA ! Sejak tahun 1988, sudah lebih dari 18000 pelatih yang telah mendapatkan sertifikasi dari American Swimming Coaches Association (ASCA).&nbsp; Mendapatkan sertifikasi ini membuktikan bahwa para pelatih di Tirta Sriwijaya Aquatic Club (TSAC) berkomitmen penuh pada pembinaan olahraga akuatik yang ada di Indonesia, khususnya kota Palembang - Sumatera Selatan. Selain berkomitmen penuh para pelatih yang mengikuti sertifikasi tersebut membuktikan bahwa mereka serius dengan profesi mereka, karena jelas ASCA merupakan asosiasi resmi yang profesional dan diakui oleh dunia untuk pelatih di olahraga akuatik, dan sertifikat yang berasal dari ASCA bisa dipakai untuk semua organisasi yang membutuhkan tenaga pelatih olahraga akuatik.&nbsp;<em>worldwide!.&nbsp;</em>Kegiatan ASCA 2018 yang belangsung di Penang-Malaysia pada tanggal 27-30 April 2018 dihadiri oleh para pelatih dari seluruh dunia (22 negara) dengan jumlah peserta sekitar 288 pelatih yang mengikuti program sertifikasi ini. Adapun negara negara yang mengikuti diantara lain : Malaysia, Indonesia, Filipina, Brunei, Singapore, Kenya, Brazil, India, Great Britain, Germany, Iran, Oman, Portugal, Swedia, Scotlandia, Finlandia, Bahrain, Canada, Japan, USA, Srilanka, dan China.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Kita patut bangga bisa memiliki kesempatan untuk mengikuti kegiatan ini, karena kita bisa dikenal oleh para pelatih dari negara lain, dan juga ini menjadi bekal bagi kita sebagai pelatih untuk terus melakukan pembinaan dengan cara dan teknik yang benar &quot;. Pungkas Anugerah Widi selaku Ketua Pembina TSAC.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<img alt=\"Image may contain: 4 people, people smiling, people standing\" class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"https://scontent-sin6-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/31433212_2090320094331046_8166522452373929984_n.jpg?_nc_cat=0&oh=727c7991377ebbd3d7d7119323d2593b&oe=5B5B7545\" /></p>\n\n<p>adapun para pelatih selain Anugerah Widi yang mengikuti kegiatan ini adalah Catrine Kalalo dan Namira Putri.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>(aw/tsac)</p>\n', 'Anugrah Widi', 'Prestasi'),
